Note:
HTML to HIR Translation Test Suite

Tests translation from HTML AST to HIR.

Total Tests: 10
:End Note

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/html/html_to_hir.runa" as Translator
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore

@Reasoning:
Counter triple shared across the HTML-to-HIR driver. Same layout as
peer test suites so a unified runner can swap test binaries with no
struct conversion.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
total at offset 0, passed at 8, failed at 16; mutated via raw
Layout.memory_set_int64 because results is shared by handle.
@End Implementation

Type called "TestResults":
    total as Integer
    passed as Integer
    failed as Integer
End Type

@Reasoning:
Top-level driver for HTML-to-HIR translation. Calls 10 named test
processes, each covering a distinct HTML construct (simple element,
attributes, nesting, text content, void elements, comments, entities,
DOCTYPE, multiple children, attribute-without-value). Distinct named
test procs make a failure log immediately identify which HTML feature
regressed.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocate TestResults, print banner, run all 10 test_* procs against
the shared results buffer, print summary, return 1 if any test failed
else 0.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- All 10 named HTML forms translate to non-null HIR -> exit 0
- Any single test_* returns 0 -> results.failed >= 1 -> exit 1
@End TestCases

Process called "main" returns Integer:
    Let results be a value of type TestResults with total as 0, passed as 0, failed as 0

    proc print_header

    proc test_simple_element with results
    proc test_element_with_attributes with results
    proc test_nested_elements with results
    proc test_text_content with results
    proc test_void_element with results
    proc test_comment with results
    proc test_entity with results
    proc test_doctype with results
    proc test_multiple_children with results
    proc test_attribute_without_value with results

    proc print_results with results

    If results.failed is greater than 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Baseline: a single empty element with matching open/close tags. If
this doesn't translate, no later test will work.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Increment total. Build "<div></div>". translate_html_to_hir(source, 0).
Non-null -> [PASS]+passed; null -> [FAIL]+failed. Frees source on both
paths.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- Input "<div></div>" -> non-null HIR, passed += 1
- Translator returns 0 on a trivial element -> "Simple element: translation failed"
@End TestCases

Process called "test_simple_element" takes results as Integer returns Integer:
    Let _rtot1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 0, _rtot1 plus 1

    Let source be proc string_duplicate from StringCore with "<div></div>"
    Let hir be proc translate_html_to_hir from Translator with source, 0

    If hir is not equal to 0:
        proc print_test_success with "Simple element"
        proc deallocate from Layout with source
        Let _rpas1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 8
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 8, _rpas1 plus 1
        Return 1
    End If

    proc print_test_failure with "Simple element: translation failed"
    proc deallocate from Layout with source
    Let _rfal1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 16
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 16, _rfal1 plus 1

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Verifies multi-attribute parsing: an opening tag with two double-quoted
attributes must produce an HIR node that holds both. Catches a
regression where the attribute loop exits after the first key=value
pair.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Increment total. Build `<div class="container" id="main"></div>`.
Translator with 0 arena. Branch on hir != 0; free source on both paths.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- Input with two attributes -> non-null HIR, passed += 1
- Translator drops the second attribute and fails -> failed += 1
@End TestCases

Process called "test_element_with_attributes" takes results as Integer returns Integer:
    Let _rtot1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 0, _rtot1 plus 1

    Let source be proc string_duplicate from StringCore with "<div class=\"container\" id=\"main\"></div>"
    Let hir be proc translate_html_to_hir from Translator with source, 0

    If hir is not equal to 0:
        proc print_test_success with "Element with attributes"
        proc deallocate from Layout with source
        Let _rpas1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 8
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 8, _rpas1 plus 1
        Return 1
    End If

    proc print_test_failure with "Element with attributes: failed"
    proc deallocate from Layout with source
    Let _rfal1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 16
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 16, _rfal1 plus 1

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Verifies recursive descent through child elements. The translator must
recurse into the <p> child while still being inside the <div> parent.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Increment total. Build "<div><p>Hello</p></div>". Translator with
0 arena. Branch on hir != 0; free source on both paths.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- Input "<div><p>Hello</p></div>" -> non-null HIR with a parent-child
  structure, passed += 1
- Translator fails to recurse and yields null -> failed += 1
@End TestCases

