@Reasoning:
Verifies the HTML5 short DOCTYPE declaration translates successfully.
DOCTYPE has unique parsing rules (it starts with <! not <) so this
catches a lexer regression where the document-type token is missed.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Increment total. Build "<!DOCTYPE html>". Translator with 0 arena.
Branch on hir != 0; free source on both paths.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- Input "<!DOCTYPE html>" -> non-null HIR with DOCTYPE node, passed += 1
- Lexer fails to detect <! as the DOCTYPE start -> translator returns 0
  -> failed += 1
@End TestCases

