End Process

@Reasoning:
Verifies sibling children at the same depth are all retained. A
regression where the child loop exits after the first sibling would
silently truncate lists, tables, and other multi-row HTML structures.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Increment total. Build "<ul><li>One</li><li>Two</li></ul>". Translator
with 0 arena. Branch on hir != 0; free source on both paths.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- Input "<ul><li>One</li><li>Two</li></ul>" -> non-null HIR with two
  child <li> nodes, passed += 1
- Translator drops second <li> and either succeeds (silent corruption)
  or returns 0 -> failed += 1
@End TestCases

