@Reasoning:
Verifies HTML's boolean attribute form (e.g. "checked" with no =value).
HTML5 allows attributes to appear bare; if the parser requires every
attribute to have a value, the translator will reject perfectly valid
markup.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Increment total. Build `<input type="checkbox" checked />`. Translator
with 0 arena. Branch on hir != 0; free source on both paths.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- Input `<input type="checkbox" checked />` -> non-null HIR with
  "checked" attribute present (value may be true or empty), passed += 1
- Parser rejects bare attribute -> translator returns 0 -> failed += 1
@End TestCases

